# 🤖 Myra — Career Guidance Chatbot

> An AI-powered career guidance assistant for Pakistani students, built with Flask + Google Gemini API.


## 📌 About

**Myra** is a smart chatbot designed for students in Pakistan to help them navigate career decisions, exam preparation, and course selection. It was originally built as part of the **Jawad Institute Student Guidance Portal**.

Myra combines **rule-based responses** for common queries with **Google Gemini AI** for complex, open-ended study and career questions — giving students fast, structured, and helpful answers.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🎓 Career guidance for students after Matric, FSc, ICS
- 📝 Exam info — MDCAT, ECAT, NTS, CSS, GAT, GRE
- 💡 Study tips, course selection, and degree guidance
- 🏫 University and admission guidance
- 🔤 Abbreviation normalization (`cs` → `computer science`, `fsc` → `pre-engineering`)
- 🤖 Google Gemini AI fallback for complex queries
- 💬 HTML-formatted bot responses (bullets, bold, lists)
- ⌨️ Typing indicator animation
- 🔔 Toast notifications (success/error)
- 📱 Fully responsive design with dark mode support
- 👋 Dynamic welcome message on load

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer      | Technology                        |
|------------|-----------------------------------|
| Backend    | Python, Flask, Flask-CORS         |
| AI Model   | Google Gemini API (gemini-1.5-flash) |
| Frontend   | HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript   |
| Deployment | PythonAnywhere                    |

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
CHATBOT/
├── api_rulebased.py     # Flask backend — rule-based logic + Gemini AI fallback
├── rulebased.py         # Python class-based chatbot with regex pattern matching
├── index.html           # Chat UI — welcome message, typing indicator, toasts
├── style.css            # Responsive CSS with dark mode support
├── script.js            # Frontend JS class (MyraChatbot) — API calls & rendering
├── .env                 # Environment variables (not committed)
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Local Setup

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/myra-chatbot.git
cd myra-chatbot
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install flask flask-cors google-generativeai python-dotenv
```

### 3. Create `.env` file

```env
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
```

> Get your free Gemini API key from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/)

### 4. Run the backend

```bash
python api_rulebased.py
```

Flask will start at `http://localhost:5000`

### 5. Open frontend

Open `index.html` directly in your browser or serve it with any static server.

> ⚠️ Make sure `script.js` has `apiBaseUrl = "http://localhost:5000/api"` for local development.

---

## 🚀 PythonAnywhere Deployment

1. Upload all files to PythonAnywhere via the **Files** tab
2. In the **Web** tab, set:
   - **Source code**: `/home/yourusername/myra-chatbot`
   - **WSGI file**: point to `api_rulebased.py`
3. Set environment variable `GEMINI_API_KEY` in the WSGI config or `.env`
4. Update `script.js`:
   ```javascript
   this.apiBaseUrl = "https://yourusername.pythonanywhere.com/api";
   ```
5. Click **Reload** in the Web tab

---

## 🔌 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint                     | Description                        |
|--------|------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| POST   | `/api/chat`                  | Send a message, get bot reply      |
| GET    | `/api/careers`               | List available career options      |
| GET    | `/api/exams/<stream>`        | Get exams for a stream (cs/medical/engineering) |
| GET    | `/api/skills/<stream>`       | Get skills for a stream            |
| GET    | `/api/recommendations/<id>`  | Get personalized recommendations   |
| POST   | `/api/appointment`           | Book a teacher appointment         |
| POST   | `/api/feedback`              | Submit feedback                    |
| POST   | `/api/user/profile`          | Update user profile                |

### Example Request

```json
POST /api/chat
{
  "message": "What is the scope of computer science in Pakistan?"
}
```

### Example Response

```json
{
  "reply": "<b>Computer Science</b> has excellent scope in Pakistan:<ul><li>💻 Software Development</li><li>🤖 AI & Machine Learning</li><li>☁️ Cloud Computing</li></ul>"
}
```

